1 olive oil
1 packet freekeh
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 leek
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Beef Rump
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ tbs honey
1 sachet Zesty Chilli Salt
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Toast freekeh, stirring occasionally, until golden, 1-2 minutes.
• Half-fill the saucepan with water, then add a good pinch of salt. Bring to the boil, then simmer, uncovered, until tender, 30-35 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and return freekeh to the pan. Cover to keep warm.

TIP: The freekeh is cooked when it has softened but still retains some bite.

• Cut carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small chunks. Thickly slice leek.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

TIP: Beetroot stays firm when cooked. It's done when you can pierce it with a fork.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop roasted almonds.
• Place beef between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened. Season with salt and pepper.
• In a medium bowl, combine Aussie spice blend, a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. Add beef and turn to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate to rest.

• When the veggies are done, transfer them to the saucepan with freekeh. Add baby spinach leaves, the honey, zesty chilli salt and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste and stir to combine.

• Slice beef rump.
• Divide honey-roasted veggie freekeh between bowls. Top with beef.
• Garnish with almonds. Serve with Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!